
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-krishnan-intarea-ra-dhcp-00.txt'>
    <title>"Carrying DHCP options over Neighbor Discovery Messages", Suresh Krishnan</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-krishnan-intarea-ra-dhcp-00.txt</link>
    <description>DHCP options are used to convey network and host configuration information to the hosts attached to a network.  Some networks may wish to configure their routers to advertise these same pieces of information, and might use IPv6 Router Advertisements do distribute these parameters.  This document defines a generic neighbor discovery option for carrying DHCP options.  This option is carried over IPv6 Router Advertisements.</description>
    <dc:date>2007-11-12T08:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
